





TO: Calder Willingham

CC, 1 p.





Goldwin Smith Hall

Ithaca, NY.

March 30, 1958

Dear Mr. Willingham,

I had started to read a library copy of TO EAT A PEACH when I received your sumptuous gift for which I thank you very warmly. I thought Daddy and the Bowel Expert came out marvelously well; but I am not quite sure of the artistic validity and necessity of the intercourse scene at the end. I then turned to NATURAL CHILD and came into closer contact with your magnificent talent. The st